flattie
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:(informal) a) a flat-bottomed rowing boat.
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1920 Marlborough Sounds A flat-bottomed, and flat-sided, rowing-boat of simple construction, suited to shallows and mud-flats.
